This paper is related to wireless communications and optimization, which are topics covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems, including the analysis of signal-to-noise ratio. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) are also relevant as they cover the design and optimization of wireless communication systems. cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible categories as they may involve the use of optimization techniques for multimedia signal processing or machine learning applications in wireless communications.
